  "text": "The cross-validated measure of performance used here is a generalized version of the validated R 2 of [CITATION_1] . This measure of prediction allows for direct comparisons between proposed models. Furthermore, it should also be noted that we use this measure of performance not only to find the optimal bandwidth in non-and semi-parametric regression but also to select the best model. While we find our cross-validated measure of prediction to work well for our specific application, cross-validation and other data driven measures of model selection may lead to models that are too complex (see, for 4 example, Shao (1993) or [CITATION_2] ).",
